Police said the five-star Mandarin Oriental hotel was being evacuated and it was not yet known whether there had been any injuries. LONDON - Twenty fire engines and 120 firefighters and officers have been called to a blaze on the roof of a hotel in Knightsbridge, central London, the London Fire Brigade said on Wednesday. The cause of the blaze was not yet known, it added. A Reuters reporter said smoke was visible coming from the five-star Mandarin Oriental hotel. Police said the hotel was being evacuated and it was not yet known whether there had been any injuries.